title: 1983–84 Eastern Counties Football League
text:
The 1983–84 Eastern Counties Football League season was the 42nd in the history of <a href="Eastern%20Counties%20Football%20League">Eastern Counties Football League</a> a <a href="association%20football">football</a> competition in England.
League Table.
The league featured 22 clubs which competed in the league last season, no new clubs joined the league this season.
Braintree changed name to <a href="Braintree%20Town%20F.C.">Braintree Town</a>, Stowmarket changed name to <a href="Stowmarket%20Town%20F.C.">Stowmarket Town</a>.
